explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the development of a target exposome protocol for characterizing gestational exposure to contaminants of emerging concern (CECs) and their association with gestational diabetes mellitus (GDM). The methods used include liquid-liquid extraction-based sample preparation and liquid chromatography-tandem mass spectrometry (LC-MS/MS) analysis, along with Bayesian kernel machine regression analysis. None of the provided keywords related to machine learning, neural networks, or other advanced computational techniques are mentioned or implied in the title or abstract.
